sentence: Among the underlying components of the Russell 3000 index, we saw noteworthy options trading volume today in Greif Inc (Symbol: GEF), where a total of 1,028 contracts have traded so far, representing approximately 102,800 underlying shares.
That amounts to about 42.1% of GEF's average daily trading volume over the past month of 244,250 shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $40 strike call option expiring April 17, 2020, with 410 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 41,000 underlying shares of GEF.

Particularly high volume was seen for the $110 strike put option expiring October 18, 2019, with 12,429 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 1.2 million underlying shares of PG.
